{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"role":"symbol","title":"overlayBounds","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}]},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310).","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","title":"overlayBounds","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","title":"MLNOverlay","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"type":"topic